  "response": "**Personalized Meal Recommendations**\n=====================================\n\nBased on the provided user profile and requirements, I have created a personalized meal plan to support muscle gain for our client. The meal plan is tailored to be vegetarian and utilizes foods commonly available in Gujarat.\n\n**Breakfast**\n-------------\n\n*   **Tapioca Idli with Oats and Banana**: Approx Calories: 350, Approx Protein: 10g\n    *   Tapioca idlis are a popular breakfast option in Gujarat. This dish provides complex carbohydrates for energy and some protein from the oats.\n*   **Why it was selected:** Tapioca idlis are easy to digest, providing sustained energy throughout the morning.\n\n**Morning Snack**\n-----------------\n\n*   **Makhana with Almonds and Dates**: Approx Calories: 200, Approx Protein: 8g\n    *   Makhana (fox nuts) provide a good source of protein and fiber. Paired with almonds for added crunch and dates for natural sweetness.\n*   **Why it was selected:** Makhana is rich in carbohydrates and provides sustained energy between meals.\n\n**Lunch**\n---------\n\n*   **Brown Rice and Lentil Salad**: Approx Calories: 400, Approx Protein: 20g\n    *   Brown rice and lentils provide a balance of complex carbohydrates and protein. This salad also includes vegetables for added fiber and nutrients.\n*   **Why it was selected:** Brown rice is easy to digest, while lentils provide a good source of plant-based protein.\n\n**Evening Snack**\n-----------------\n\n*   **Roasted Chickpeas with Peanut Butter**: Approx Calories: 250, Approx Protein: 12g\n    *   Roasted chickpeas are crunchy and provide a good source of plant-based protein. Paired with peanut butter for added healthy fats.\n*   **Why it was selected:** Roasted chickpeas are low in calories but high in fiber and protein.\n\n**Dinner**\n---------\n\n*   **Vegetable Biryani with Tofu**: Approx Calories: 450, Approx Protein: 25g\n    *   Vegetable biryani is a popular Gujarati dish made with mixed vegetables. Adding tofu provides plant-based protein.\n*   **Why it was selected:** This meal provides complex carbohydrates from the rice and fiber-rich vegetables.\n\n**Snacks**\n------------\n\n*   **Trail Mix**: Approx Calories: 150, Approx Protein: 6g\n    *   Trail mix is a convenient snack option containing nuts, seeds, and dried fruits. Paired with plant-based protein powder for added protein.\n*   **Why it was selected:** Trail mix provides sustained energy between meals.\n\n**Supplement Recommendations**\n-----------------------------\n\n*   Plant-Based Protein Powder: To support muscle growth and provide additional protein during workouts.\n*   **Why it was selected:** This supplement supports muscle gain while adhering to the vegetarian diet.\n\nBy following this personalized meal plan, our client will be able to meet their daily calorie and protein targets while supporting muscle gain. The meal plan is practical, easy to digest, and utilizes foods commonly available in Gujarat.",
